<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +5, Stealth +3</p>

<p><strong>Damage Immunities</strong> cold</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Giant, Winter Wolf</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 3 (700 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Keen Hearing and Smell.</em></strong> The wolf has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on hearing or smell.</p>

<p><strong><em>Pack Tactics.</em></strong> The wolf has advantage on an attack roll against a creature if at least one of the wolf’s allies is within 5 ft. of the creature and the ally isn’t incapacitated.</p>

<p><strong><em>Snow Camouflage.</em></strong> The wolf has advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in snowy terrain.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Bite.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 11 (2d6 + 4) piercing damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a DC 14 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone.</p>

<p><strong><em>Cold Breath (Recharge 5-6).</em></strong> The wolf exhales a blast of freezing wind in a 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 12 Dexterity saving throw, taking 18 (4d8) cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>

